  "body": "View this post on the web at https://www.whytryai.com/p/sunday-rundown-138-agentic-tasks\r\n\r\nHappy Sunday, friends!\r\nWelcome back to the weekly AI news roundup.\r\nIn case you missed it, here’s this week’s Thursday deep dive:\r\nIf you’re consistently missing out on my emails, remember to check your “Promotions” tab and mark whytryai@substack.com as a “Safe Sender.”\r\n🗞️ AI news\r\nHere’s what happened in AI this week:\r\n👩‍💻 AI releases\r\nAlibaba open-sourced Qwen3.6-27B, a cost-efficient 27B model that outperforms much larger ones on agentic coding tasks [ https://substack.com/redirect/3e6c36c7-2db7-4e8e-aad1-3ebe7c9c58f3?j=eyJ1IjoiMWllZnkifQ.sG3OqnkHDNZpplC0eLA9u0NYhAE4J8yHwSPDyeVA8k8 ].\r\nAnthropic news:\r\nClaude Connectors expanded to 200+ everyday apps [ https://substack.com/redirect/b63774dc-e02c-4ac7-b11d-c21e1be279f5?j=eyJ1IjoiMWllZnkifQ.sG3OqnkHDNZpplC0eLA9u0NYhAE4J8yHwSPDyeVA8k8 ], letting Claude pull in relevant data mid-chat and chain multiple services together.\r\nCowork can now build Live Artifacts: dashboards and trackers connected to your data sources [ https://substack.com/redirect/c93d2525-d1d4-42bf-b555-100d61e843b8?j=eyJ1IjoiMWllZnkifQ.sG3OqnkHDNZpplC0eLA9u0NYhAE4J8yHwSPDyeVA8k8 ] that auto-refresh when opened.\r\nDeepSeek open-sourced DeepSeek-V4, a reasoning model with a 1M-token context window [ https://substack.com/redirect/1031ecd9-903c-4a58-8c34-1ca56fdb89a0?j=eyJ1IjoiMWllZnkifQ.sG3OqnkHDNZpplC0eLA9u0NYhAE4J8yHwSPDyeVA8k8 ] that approaches the performance of top-tier closed models.\r\nGoogle news:\r\nAI Studio now gives Google AI Pro and Ultra subscribers higher usage limits and new models [ https://substack.com/redirect/872c1465-3a6a-4c7c-b2c6-b0d183749fb4?j=eyJ1IjoiMWllZnkifQ.sG3OqnkHDNZpplC0eLA9u0NYhAE4J8yHwSPDyeVA8k8 ] for prototyping and vibe-coding projects.\r\nDeep Research and Deep Research Max can perform autonomous research across your files or specialized data sources [ https://substack.com/redirect/d019ee58-4f18-4186-abb1-953af526a659?j=eyJ1IjoiMWllZnkifQ.sG3OqnkHDNZpplC0eLA9u0NYhAE4J8yHwSPDyeVA8k8 ] using MCP connections.\r\nGemini for Home added a Continued Conversation feature that lets your smart speaker retain context after a response [ https://substack.com/redirect/e1d4a531-f692-4b88-9045-6f9c7ed45068?j=eyJ1IjoiMWllZnkifQ.sG3OqnkHDNZpplC0eLA9u0NYhAE4J8yHwSPDyeVA8k8 ] and handle follow-up questions.\r\nMicrosoft added Copilot’s agentic capabilities to Excel, PowerPoint, and Word, letting it perform multi-step actions directly in your documents [ https://substack.com/redirect/e11be622-bba2-4f77-b9ac-3b46a2c447d8?j=eyJ1IjoiMWllZnkifQ.sG3OqnkHDNZpplC0eLA9u0NYhAE4J8yHwSPDyeVA8k8 ].\r\nMoonshot AI open-sourced Kimi K2.6, a coding model that can coordinate 300 simultaneous sub-agents [ https://substack.com/redirect/3adf79a6-affe-41e3-8fa1-dc026f6c0fc1?j=eyJ1IjoiMWllZnkifQ.sG3OqnkHDNZpplC0eLA9u0NYhAE4J8yHwSPDyeVA8k8 ] for complex, long-horizon programming projects.\r\nOpenAI news:\r\nChatGPT for Clinicians helps verified US physicians, nurse practitioners, and pharmacists with medical research and documentation work [ https://substack.com/redirect/6a62f1fb-da3d-4c29-8997-c7a3dae566e0?j=eyJ1IjoiMWllZnkifQ.sG3OqnkHDNZpplC0eLA9u0NYhAE4J8yHwSPDyeVA8k8 ].\r\nChatGPT Images 2.0 is a SOTA image-generation model [ https://substack.com/redirect/e968e70a-0886-47f4-8af4-1df86cca1397?j=eyJ1IjoiMWllZnkifQ.sG3OqnkHDNZpplC0eLA9u0NYhAE4J8yHwSPDyeVA8k8 ] with thinking capabilities that can reason through your prompts.\r\nCodex Chronicle builds context from your screen activity [ https://substack.com/redirect/767ef40f-cb0b-4cf7-8887-f9841335f595?j=eyJ1IjoiMWllZnkifQ.sG3OqnkHDNZpplC0eLA9u0NYhAE4J8yHwSPDyeVA8k8 ], so Codex knows what you’re working on automatically. (Opt-in preview for Pro subscribers.)\r\nGPT-5.5 is a flagship model for complex coding, research, and data analysis [ https://substack.com/redirect/bdf28d99-4770-4652-8e81-6db03c25b06d?j=eyJ1IjoiMWllZnkifQ.sG3OqnkHDNZpplC0eLA9u0NYhAE4J8yHwSPDyeVA8k8 ] that is also more token-efficient than competing models.\r\nWorkspace Agents let teams build shared AI agents for long-running tasks [ https://substack.com/redirect/1f11a1a0-d9f7-4151-b152-934b045fc550?j=eyJ1IjoiMWllZnkifQ.sG3OqnkHDNZpplC0eLA9u0NYhAE4J8yHwSPDyeVA8k8 ] in the cloud. (For ChatGPT for Business, Enterprise, and Edu plans.)\r\nTwelveLabs launched Pegasus 1.5, which extracts structured, timestamped metadata from videos [ https://substack.com/redirect/ba48afec-3eb3-402c-86b5-cca9d72e5a29?j=eyJ1IjoiMWllZnkifQ.sG3OqnkHDNZpplC0eLA9u0NYhAE4J8yHwSPDyeVA8k8 ] up to two hours long so you can better analyze them.\r\nX launched Custom Timelines that lets you pin up to 75+ AI-curated topics [ https://substack.com/redirect/4bad1771-ea49-4216-8b24-203689063012?j=eyJ1IjoiMWllZnkifQ.sG3OqnkHDNZpplC0eLA9u0NYhAE4J8yHwSPDyeVA8k8 ] to your home tab. (In early access for Premium subscribers.)\r\n🔬 AI research\r\nAlibaba announced Qwen3.6-Max-Preview, with improved agentic coding, world knowledge, and instruction following [ https://substack.com/redirect/c441bb5b-893a-41e5-8578-d46d32a43b4b?j=eyJ1IjoiMWllZnkifQ.sG3OqnkHDNZpplC0eLA9u0NYhAE4J8yHwSPDyeVA8k8 ] for real-world tasks.\r\n📖 AI resources\r\n“GPT 5.5, DeepSeek V4, and the Compute War [ https://substack.com/redirect/abef08db-f33c-46ec-9e8b-2271903523e5?j=eyJ1IjoiMWllZnkifQ.sG3OqnkHDNZpplC0eLA9u0NYhAE4J8yHwSPDyeVA8k8 ]” [VIDEO]: great level-headed deep-dive by AI Explained.\r\n🤦‍♂️ AI fail of the week\r\nWell, at least you’re aware of your own limitations, Gemini.\r\nWhy Try AI is proudly reader-supported. Subscribe to get every future post. Go paid to unlock extra stuff [ https://substack.com/redirect/78bf8618-e779-41e5-9be7-5d8114a0cb2e?j=eyJ1IjoiMWllZnkifQ.sG3OqnkHDNZpplC0eLA9u0NYhAE4J8yHwSPDyeVA8k8 ].\r\n📹 Live & Learn #3: AI Slide Deck Makers\r\nThe “Live & Learn” format is really coming into its own, thanks to great feedback from everyone who responded to my surveys. Keep your suggestions coming!\r\nFrom now on, there’s more structure to my live tests and the scoring.\r\nFuture “Live & Learn” sessions will:\r\nFocus on 3-5 tools in the same category for an apples-to-apples comparison\r\nHave 3-5 specific dimensions we rate them on\r\nWrap-up with a leaderboard we fill out together during the session\r\nThis week, we tested five AI slide deck makers and ended with a two-way tie for first place:\r\nNext time, we’ll be testing AI tools that automatically create helpful visuals like charts and diagrams out of text. It’s happening on Friday, May 1, at 2:00 PM CET.\r\nPlease let me know what you want to get out of this particular session and “Live & Learn” in general:\r\n(It’s just two open-ended questions with a few AI-assisted follow-ups.)\r\nThanks!\r\n\r\nUnsubscribe https://substack..X5wZn9TOldi7jFwc_4LMZ321oJbj6sk8a_kPQ-JceE8?",
